===Etymology===
Japanese [[三味線]] ([[さみせん]]), from Chinese [[三弦]] ''sānxián'', from ''sān'' ‘three’ + ''xián'' ‘string’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'sæmɪsɛn/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|samisen|samisens}}
# a kind of three-stringed Japanese [[lute]]
#:*'''1982''': He sees her chastened and cast-down eyes as she kneels and tinkles away on her '''samisen''' — John Fowles, ''Mantissa''

